title: Binary Search
description: Given an array of integers nums which is sorted in ascending order, and an integer target, write a function to search target in nums. If target exists, then return its index. Otherwise, return -1. You must write an algorithm with O(log n) runtime complexity.
input_format: The first line contains integers separated by space (nums). The second line contains the target integer.
output_format: A single integer representing the index or -1.

constraints.uniqueness: All the integers in nums are unique.
constraints.sorted: nums is sorted in ascending order.
